-- Liverpool Targets Barcelona’s Montoya, Mirror Says: Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-10-18T09:52:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-18/liverpool-targets-barcelona-s-montoya-mirror-says-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Barcelona Defender  Liverpool is preparing a bid for Barcelona right-back
Martin Montoya, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The 22-year-old is also a target for Bayern Munich and
Bayer Leverkusen, the Mirror said.  Liverpool Loan  Valencia wants to sign Liverpool’s Tiago Llori on loan
after the 20-year-old central defender failed to win a regular
team berth,  the Daily Express  reported.  Llori joined the Reds from Sporting Lisbon for 7 million
pounds in the offseason, the Express said.  Old Trafford  Manchester United executive Ed Woodward will look into
reintroducing a standing area for fans at Old Trafford,  the
Independent  reported.  It adds impetus by a campaign to overturn a 1989 regulation
that says stadiums in  England ’s top two divisions must have only
seating, the Independent said.  Carroll’s Physio  West Ham’s 6-foot-3 striker Andy Carroll is receiving
physiotherapy in Antwerp from a Belgian who also works with
ballet dancers, the  Daily Mail  reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
